The paper deals with the problem of positioning using antenna arrays deployed as a large intelligent surface (LIS), which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields such as information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), machine learning (cs.MA), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Fisher-informations and Cramer-Rao lower bounds (CRLB) also suggests a focus on statistical signal processing and estimation theory, which are typically associated with cs.IT and cs.SY.
